Parillada - - This is an area of two ruined huts near the only spring on the ridge between the Río Isi Taxaña and Río Quenhuani (the former not on a map, the later misplaced where the former actually is). The area is 1.5 km W. of the mouth of the Río Aguilani (also misplaced on map!!) at Laka Chaka 20 km N. of Choquetanga. Area of newly discovered (today) agricultural terraces following a ridge down through head high grasses with scattered Bombaceae trees, to a newly discovered forteleza above the Río Isi Taxaña which is covered in a tangle of thorn scrub.

Parillada - Slopes between Lakea Chaka and mouth of Río Khewani 12 km S of Miguillas.

Mikailpurhua - - If one follows the trail from Laka Chaka at the mouth of the Río Aguilani on the way to Khora, about 4 hours on foot (3.5 km crow flies) to the NNE one crosses two rivers. The north fork is the Río Aguada, the south fork is the Mikhailpurhua. 24 km N of Choquetanga. Very diverse riverine forest with everything from Sorocea to Boehmeria. Semi ever-green.

Huayra Pata - - Major ruin discovery of large fortelezas, irrigation canals and mysterious foundations cover this ridge which is 2 km NE of the mouth of the Río Aguilani mouth at Lakachaka, and 2 km S. of the junction of the Río Mikhailpurhua and Río Aguada. 22 km N. of Choquetanga. Area of ancient ruins which has been overgrazed, burned and generally raped into semi-barren grassland with some small shrubs. Collected bordering woodlanads and mattorales
